The rules and regulations shall provide for the licensing of home health agencies and annual license renewal, and shall establish standards that require as a minimum, that all home health agencies:
Within 10 days of acceptance of a patient for skilled care, make and record all reasonable efforts to contact a physician to obtain the signed order required under item (2) of this subsection;
That accept patients for skilled care do so only on the signed order of a physician obtained within 28 days after acceptance;
Adopt procedures for the administration of drugs and biologicals;
Maintain clinical records on all patients accepted for skilled care;
Establish patient care policies and personnel policies;
Have services available at least 8 hours a day, 5 days a week, and available on an emergency basis 24 hours a day, 7 days a week;
Make service available to an individual in need within 24 hours of a referral when stipulated by a physician's order;
Have a designated supervisor of patient care who is a full-time employee of the agency and is available at all times during operating hours and additionally as needed; and
Have as the administrator of the agency a person who has at least 1 year of supervisory experience in hospital management, home health management, or public health program management and who is:
A licensed physician;
A registered nurse; or
A college graduate with a bachelor's degree in a health-related field.

The rules and regulations may include provisions that:
Deal with the establishment of home health agencies;
Require each home health agency to have its policies established by a professional group that includes at least:
1 physician;
1 registered nurse;
1 representative of another offered service; and
1 public member;
Govern the services provided by the home health agencies;
Require keeping clinical records of each patient, including the plan of treatment to be provided;
Govern supervision of the services, as appropriate, by:
A physician;
A registered nurse; or
Another health professional who is qualified sufficiently by advanced training to supervise the same kind of services in a hospital; and
Require submission of an annual report which includes service utilization statistics.
